        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Marshall, or near Hot Springs. This storm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs, Allenstand, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
